      <hedline>
        <hl1>Put Milosevic on Trial</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Seth Trueger letter says Slobodan Milosevic, who has been indicted on war-crimes charges, should be given fair trial before international court</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An Oct. 12 letter states that ''reigniting nationalist sentiments for the sake of a trial at The Hague for Mr. Milosevic is simply not worth the price.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>An Oct. 12 letter states that ''reigniting nationalist sentiments for the sake of a trial at The Hague for Mr. Milosevic is simply not worth the price.''</p>
        <p>Slobodan Milosevic has been indicted on war-crimes charges, accused of having been responsible for the deaths of at least hundreds of innocents. What message are we sending if we let him free?</p>
        <p>He should be given a fair trial before an international court in the name of justice. There is no excuse for war crimes.</p>
        <p>SETH TRUEGER  Ithaca, N.Y., Oct. 12, 2000</p>
      </block>
